Interface IMleCallback

  • All Known Subinterfaces:

    public interface IMleCallback
    This interface specifies a generic callback prototype.
    Author:
    Mark S. Millard

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void enable(boolean enable)

    • Method Detail

      • isEnabled

        boolean isEnabled()
        Determine whether the callback handler is enabled.
        Returns:
        true is returned if the callback is enabled. Otherwise, false will be returned.

      • enable

        void enable(boolean enable)
        Enable the callback.
        Parameters:
        enable - true should be used if the callback is to be enabled. Otherwise, false should be used to disable the callback.
